    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Neckwear that resembles a short chemisette, meant to cover a woman's neck and chest. Often white, and made in a variety of fabrics. For headwear that envelops the head, chin, sides of the face, and neck, and retained as headwear by nuns, use 'wimples'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
